level.code:
FLOAT variables store numbers with decimal points. half = 0.5 three = 3.0
sum = half + three If you try to assign a float to an integer the decimal and following numbers are erased int_sum = (int)(half + three)
You can also assign integer values to float variables Remember, floats always have a decimal point, even if it's 0! new_three = (float)int_sum;
